Description: The Next Generation Science Standards is a national effort to create new education standards.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, Southern US
Full Description: The Next Generation Science Standards is a national effort to create new education standards. The purpose of these standards include: combating ignorance of science, creating common standards for teaching in the U.S., and developing greater interest in science among students so that more of them choose to major in science and technology in college. The Next Generation Science Standards (NGSS) are based on the ""Framework Kâ12 Science Education"" that was created by the National Research Council. It has three dimensions that are integrated in instruction at all levels. The first is core ideas which consist of specific content and subject areas. The second is science and engineering practices where students are expected not just to learn content but to understand the methods of scientists and engineers. The third is cross-cutting concepts that include key underlying ideas that are common to a number of topics. The NGSS give equal emphasis to engineering design and to scientific inquiry.

Description: Mobile Broadband for the Sharing Economy
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: RovAir shares mobile broadband among unrelated users, delivering on-demand mobile broadband whenever needed and for any âtimeâ period. We eliminate the need to understand how much data is needed as our billing is based solely on time and NOT megabytes (MB) or GB.  RovAir is mobile broadband in the Sharing Economy. Often referred to as collaborative consumption, the Sharing Economy recognizes where resources are underutilized, and creates an opportunity to share these resources with others. It is a model where âaccess trumps ownershipâ delivering data resources to many more users, whenever and wherever they desire.  RovAir was founded in 2007 as a mobile broadband rental company, one of the first to do this. A rapid evolution of the wireless industry, RovAir scaled back and went into hibernation for several years before relaunching as a mobile broadband on demand service. Ultimately, we envision a world that can interactively share data among completely unrelated users on a peer to peer level. We are working hard to make this reality.
